<li id="cite_note-detest-6"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-detest_6-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFWatterson1990" class="citation web cs1"><a href="/wiki/Bill_Watterson" title="Bill Watterson">Watterson, Bill</a> (May 20, 1990). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20060219183419/http://home3.inet.tele.dk/stadil/spe_kc.htm">"Speech by Bill Watterson"</a>. Kenyon College, <a href="/wiki/Gambier,_Ohio" title="Gambier, Ohio">Gambier, Ohio</a>: Via Calvin and Hobbes' Magical World (fan site). Archived from <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://home3.inet.tele.dk/stadil/spe_kc.htm">the original</a> on February 19, 2006<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">March 16,</span> 2006</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Speech+by+Bill+Watterson&amp;rft.place=Kenyon+College%2C+Gambier%2C+Ohio&amp;rft.pub=Via+Calvin+and+Hobbes%27+Magical+World+%28fan+site%29&amp;rft.date=1990-05-20&amp;rft.aulast=Watterson&amp;rft.aufirst=Bill&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fhome3.inet.tele.dk%2Fstadil%2Fspe_kc.htm&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACalvin+and+Hobbes" class="Z3988"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r951705291"/></span>
</li>
