<li id="cite_note-krulwich2011-122"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-krulwich2011_122-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFKrulwich2011" class="citation web cs1"><a href="/wiki/Robert_Krulwich" title="Robert Krulwich">Krulwich, Robert</a> (May 31, 2011). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.npr.org/sections/krulwich/2011/05/31/136817328/calvin-hobbes-and-comic-book-biology">"Calvin, Hobbes And Comic Book Biology"</a>. <i>Krulwich Wonders..</i>. Washington, D.C.: <a href="/wiki/NPR" title="NPR">NPR</a>. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20150912150150/http://www.npr.org/sections/krulwich/2011/05/31/136817328/calvin-hobbes-and-comic-book-biology">Archived</a> from the original on September 12, 2015<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">December 5,</span> 2015</span>. <q>Dan and Tom Heyerman...to the delight of many Calvin and Hobbes fans...brought Calvin back...as an adult!... Not only that, he has a kid, a daughter named 'Bacon' (named for the Enlightenment philosopher, Francis Bacon.)</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Krulwich+Wonders...&amp;rft.atitle=Calvin%2C+Hobbes+And+Comic+Book+Biology&amp;rft.date=2011-05-31&amp;rft.aulast=Krulwich&amp;rft.aufirst=Robert&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2Fsections%2Fkrulwich%2F2011%2F05%2F31%2F136817328%2Fcalvin-hobbes-and-comic-book-biology&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACalvin+and+Hobbes" class="Z3988"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r951705291"/></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-krulwich2012-123"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-krulwich2012_123-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFKrulwich2012" class="citation web cs1"><a href="/wiki/Robert_Krulwich" title="Robert Krulwich">Krulwich, Robert</a> (February 15, 2012). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.npr.org/sections/krulwich/2012/02/15/146939479/calvin-and-hobbes-add-the-bacon">"Calvin And Hobbes, Add The Bacon"</a>. <i>Krulwich Wonders..</i>. Washington, D.C.: <a href="/wiki/NPR" title="NPR">NPR</a>. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20150920153452/http://www.npr.org/sections/krulwich/2012/02/15/146939479/calvin-and-hobbes-add-the-bacon">Archived</a> from the original on September 20, 2015<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">December 5,</span> 2015</span>. <q>'Hobbes and Bacon'...went instantly viral.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Krulwich+Wonders...&amp;rft.atitle=Calvin+And+Hobbes%2C+Add+The+Bacon&amp;rft.date=2012-02-15&amp;rft.aulast=Krulwich&amp;rft.aufirst=Robert&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2Fsections%2Fkrulwich%2F2012%2F02%2F15%2F146939479%2Fcalvin-and-hobbes-add-the-bacon&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACalvin+and+Hobbes" class="Z3988"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r951705291"/></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-robinson2013-124"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-robinson2013_124-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFRobinson2013" class="citation web cs1">Robinson, Tasha (March 14, 2013). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.avclub.com/article/check-out-the-web-cartoonists-continuing-icalvin-a-93700">"Check out the web cartoonists continuing <i>Calvin And Hobbes</i>"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/The_A.V._Club" title="The A.V. Club">The A.V. Club</a></i>. Chicago, Illinois: <a href="/wiki/Onion,_Inc." class="mw-redirect" title="Onion, Inc.">Onion, Inc.</a> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20150526073337/http://www.avclub.com/article/check-out-the-web-cartoonists-continuing-icalvin-a-93700">Archived</a> from the original on May 26, 2015<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">December 5,</span> 2015</span>. <q>The strips got a lot of attention when they first posted, and Watterson fans often point back to them.... Terra Snover picked it up with...strips continuing the <i>Hobbes And Bacon</i> idea... In February 2013, Phil Berry at DeviantArt started posting his own, more elaborate <i>Hobbes And Bacon</i> strips... Meanwhile, a fourth artist, DeviantArt’s DomNX, has spent the past year churning out his own still-ongoing <i>Calvin And Company</i> strip...</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=The+A.V.+Club&amp;rft.atitle=Check+out+the+web+cartoonists+continuing+Calvin+And+Hobbes&amp;rft.date=2013-03-14&amp;rft.aulast=Robinson&amp;rft.aufirst=Tasha&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.avclub.com%2Farticle%2Fcheck-out-the-web-cartoonists-continuing-icalvin-a-93700&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACalvin+and+Hobbes" class="Z3988"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r951705291"/></span>
